create(address).details: The caller of this function will become the admin of the CSR ERC20 token.

returns._0: The contract address of the newly created csrERC token contract.

returns.cscStakers: The address of the CSC stakers contract.

params.erc20: The contract address of the ERC20 token.

returns.csrERC20: The CSR enabled ERC20 token contract address. Return address(0) if the given                     contract address has not a CSR enabled ERC20 token.

params.csrERC20: The contract address of the CSR enabled ERC20 token.

returns.erc20: The ERC20 token contract address. Return address(0) if the given                     contract address is not a CSR enabled ERC20 token.

params.i: The index of the CSR enabled ERC20 token.

returns.csrERC20: The CSR enabled ERC20 token contract address.

returns.count: The number of CSR enabled ERC20 tokens created by this factory contract.

params.addr: The contract address to be verified.

returns.result: True if the contract address is a CSR enabled ERC20 token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pullFundsFromTurnstile(address).details: Pull the CSR, refund `msg.sender` the gas cost for calling this          function and distribute the rest among token holders.         If the gas cost is higher than the amount of the CSR available,         `msg.sender` will not be refunded and the full CSR amount will be         distributed.         To prevent gas price manipulation, this function is callable only         by the wallet of the team, it's sole purpose is to assure frequent         CSR distribution when no one actively call the public         `pullFundsFromTurnstile` function of the `csrERC20` token.

params.csrERC20: The CSR enabled ERC20 token contract address.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newCscStakers: The new address of the CSC stakers contract.

create(address).notice: Create a CSR enabled wrapped ERC20 token of an existing ERC20 token.

getCSCstakersAddress().notice: Get the address of the CSC stakers contract.

getCsrERC20(address).notice: Get CSR enabled ERC20 token addrress of ERC20 token.

getERC20(address).notice: Get the ERC20 token address of a CSR enabled ERC20 token.

getTokenPairById(uint256).notice: Get the ERC20 token address and CSR enabled ERC20 token address by tokens pair id.

getTokenPairsCount().notice: Get the number of CSR enabled ERC20 tokens created by this factory contract.

isCsrERC20(address).notice: Verify if a contract address is a CSR enabled ERC20 token created         by this factory contract.

pullFundsFromTurnstile(address).notice: Special function callable only by the factory contract which         pull and distribute the CSR among token holders. The purpose         of this function is to ensure the CSR gets pulled frequently         out of the box while maintaining low running cost for the team.

setCscStakers(address).notice: Set the address of the CSC stakers contract.
